8%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Minnie%20Mouse%20at%20Walt%20Disney%20World.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662549700dfb1341e9fd610d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMinnie%20Mouse%20at%20Walt%20Disney%20World.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20discovered%20that%20Savannah%20%E2%80%94%20who%20asked%20that%20her%20last%20name%20not%20be%20published%20for%20health%20privacy%20reasons%20%E2%80%94%20had%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdiseases%2F24549-os-trigonum-syndrome%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eos%20trigonum%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20an%20extra%20bone%20found%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20ankle%2C%20around%202013.%20Savannah%20had%20accidentally%20broken%20the%20os%20trigonum%20while%20running%20one%20day%20and%20didn't%20receive%20medical%20treatment%20for%20eight%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20has%20continued%20to%20cause%20her%20pain%20and%20affect%20her%20mobility.%20She's%20undergone%2016%20surgeries%20since%20she%20was%2017%2C%20including%2012%20surgeries%20on%20her%20ankles.%20Most%20recently%2C%20she%20underwent%20a%20subtalar%20fusion%20procedure%20in%20August%20after%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20rheumatoid%20arthritis%2015%20months%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESavannah%20had%20accepted%20that%20a%20Disney%20World%20vacation%20wasn't%20feasible%20until%20her%20physical%20therapist%20told%20her%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdisneyland.disney.go.com%2Fguest-services%2Fdisability-access-service%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDisney's%20Disability%20Access%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20allowed%20guests%20who%20could%20not%20stand%20in%20line%20due%20to%20a%20disability%20to%20schedule%20rides%20in%20advance%20and%20then%20wait%20somewhere%20else%20until%20it's%20their%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESavannah%20doesn't%20lack%20full%20mobility%20but%20would%20need%20frequent%20breaks%20to%20navigate%20Disney%20World%2C%20so%20the%20service%20sounded%20like%20a%20good%20solution.%20She%20and%20her%20husband%20went%20ahead%20and%20booked%20a%20vacation%20for%20May%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20that%20glimmer%20of%20hope%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Savannah%20said.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20finally%20lined%20up%2C%20and%20I%20was%20sitting%20on%20cloud%20nine.%20Then%2C%20Disney%20dropped%20that%20bombshell.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDisney's%20new%20disability%20policy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bombshell%3A%20Disney%20announced%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20it%20would%20revise%20its%20Disability%20Access%20Service%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisney's%20policy%20previously%20allowed%20anyone%20who%20had%20%26quot%3Bdifficulty%20tolerating%20extended%20waits%20in%20a%20conventional%20queue%20environment%20due%20to%20a%20disability%26quot%3B%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20program%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxbusiness.com%2Flifestyle%2Fdisney-parks-issue-lifetime-bans-people-lie-disabilities%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20service%20is%20more%20narrow%2C%20accommodating%20%26quot%3Bonly%20those%20Guests%20who%2C%20due%20to%20a%20developmental%20disability%20like%20autism%20or%20similar%2C%20are%20unable%20to%20wait%20in%20a%20conventional%20queue%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisney's%20policy%20change%20was%2C%20in%20part%2C%20an%20attempt%20to%20prevent%20able-bodied%20guests%20from%20exploiting%20the%20service.%20A%20Disney%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20last%20year%20that%20there's%20been%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-world-florida-third-party-tour-guide-crackdown-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincrease%20in%20people%20misusing%20the%20service%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20skip%20lines%20and%20avoid%20crowds.%20Disability%20services%20are%20now%20the%20most%20requested%20service%20at%20the%20California%20and%20Florida%20parks%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftravel%2F2024%2F04%2F11%2Fdisney-disability-access-service-das%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDisney%20is%20dedicated%20to%20providing%20a%20great%20experience%20for%20all%20Guests%2C%20including%20those%20with%20disabilities%2C%20which%20is%20why%20we%20are%20so%20committed%20to%20delivering%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20innovative%20support%20services%20aimed%20at%20helping%20our%20Guests%20with%20disabilities%20have%20a%20wonderful%20time%20when%20visiting%20our%20theme%20parks%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Disneyland%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223264%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Crowds%20at%20Walt%20Disney%20World%20in%20June%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66254a8b23b29110d30144ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222119%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECrowds%20at%20Walt%20Disney%20World%20in%20June%202023.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Disneyland%20and%20Disney%20World%20websites%20include%20information%20for%20individuals%20with%20disabilities%20across%20different%20categories%2C%20including%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20alternative%20for%20Savannah%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdisneyworld.disney.go.com%2Fguest-services%2Frider-switch%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERider%20Switch%20%3C%2Fa%3Eservice%2C%20which%20allows%20one%20adult%20to%20wait%20with%20non-riders%20while%20the%20remaining%20group%20members%20enjoy%20the%20attraction.%20When%20the%20guests%20return%20from%20the%20attraction%2C%20they%20can%20swap%20places%20with%20the%20waiting%20adult%2C%20who%20will%20be%20allowed%20to%20board%20the%20attraction%20without%20waiting%20in%20line%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Savannah%20said%20the%20Rider%20Switch%20service%20isn't%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20her%20because%20she%20intends%20to%20explore%20the%20park%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20meaning%20her%20mother%20would%20have%20to%20stand%20in%20the%20lines.%20%26quot%3BDoes%20she%20really%20need%20to%20stand%20in%20a%20line%20for%2075%20minutes%20for%20me%20while%20I%20sit%20isolated%20from%20my%20group%3F%26quot%3B%20Savannah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDisabled%20fans%20accuse%20Disney%20of%20discrimination%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Savannah%20and%20more%20than%20140%20others%20are%20calling%20the%20revised%20policy%20discriminatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20formal%20letter%20addressed%20to%20Disney's%20top%20brass%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbob-iger-career-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20CEO%20Bob%20Iger%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20the%20coalition%20pointed%20to%20cancer%20patients%2C%20narcoleptics%2C%20veterans%20with%20PTSD%2C%20individuals%20with%20Parkinson's%20disease%2C%20and%20other%20groups%20as%20people%20now%20excluded%20from%20Disability%20Access%20Services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPunishing%20disabled%20individuals%20for%20the%20actions%20of%20able-bodied%20individuals%20who%20abuse%20the%20system%20is%20not%20a%20solution%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20reads.%20%26quot%3BThese%20changes%20fail%20to%20adequately%20address%20abuse%3B%20people%20who%20abuse%20the%20system%20will%20still%20lie.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Walt%20Disney%20World%20crowds%20on%20April%2020%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dff293bd98a6001979e1df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221605%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWalt%20Disney%20World%20in%20April%202023.%20%3Cp%3EJoe%20Burbank%2FOrlando%20Sentinel%2FTribune%20News%20Service%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESavannah%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20changes%20have%20inadvertently%20pushed%20a%20harmful%20narrative%20about%20who%20is%20%26quot%3Bdisabled%20enough%26quot%3B%20to%20qualify.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20the%20right%20kind%20of%20disabled%20and%20you%20don't%20matter.%20That's%20the%20way%20that%20Disney%20is%20portraying%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20her%20husband%20have%20already%20saved%20%244%2C000%20and%20collected%20around%20%24400%20in%20gift%20cards%20to%20cover%20their%20vacation%20costs.%20However%2C%20the%20policy%20changes%20%E2%80%94%20scheduled%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20the%20first%20day%20of%20their%20Disney%20vacation%20%E2%80%94%20have%20upended%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20invested%20all%20of%20this%20money%20that%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20give%20me%20back%20if%20I%20can't%20physically%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Savannah%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20does%20that%20look%20like%20for%20me%3F%20It%20did%20not%20feel%20like%20the%20Disney%20that%20I%20have%20heard%20so%20many%20good%20things%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESavannah%20added%20that%20had%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20known%20about%20the%20policy%20changes%20ahead%20of%20time%2C%20they%20wouldn't%20have%20spent%20their%20time%20or%20money%20on%20Disney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20absolutely%20would%20not%20have%20gone%20to%20Disney.%20I%20would%20not%20have%20chosen%20to%20spend%20my%20money%20there.%20I%20would%20have%20spent%20my%20money%20at%20Universal%20%5BStudios%5D%2C%20where%20they%20still%20treat%20me%20like%20a%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Savannah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-world-fans-say-theme-park-disability-policy-discriminatory-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713783061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66254b7d83c8ec6e1530680c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%2