s%20social%20media%20marketing%20evolved%2C%20so%20did%20the%20opportunity%20for%20influencers%20to%20work%20with%20more%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20accepted%20deals%20with%20brands%20that%20weren't%20aligned%2C%20they%20put%20up%20campaigns%20that%20were%20not%20thought%20out%2C%20and%20consumers%20could%20tell%20that%20it%20wasn't%20aligned%2C%26quot%3B%20Rector%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20someone%20feels%20like%20you%20are%20selling%20them%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20selling%2C%20they%20inherently%20lose%20trust.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESamantha%20Zink%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20talent%20management%20agency%20Zink%20Talent%2C%20told%20BI%20the%20influencer%20industry%20has%20changed%20massively%20since%20it%20began%20in%20the%20early%20noughties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20then%2C%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bmore%20about%20passion%20than%20profit%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20while%20now%20content%20creation%20is%20a%20fully-fledged%20career%20with%20commissions%20and%20subscriptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20shift%20has%20made%20influencer%20engagements%20seem%20less%20special%20because%20what%20was%20once%20a%20hobby%20or%20a%20passion%20project%20is%20now%20a%20necessity%20to%20earn%20a%20living%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BInfluencers%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20are%20supporting%20families%2C%20must%20engage%20in%20brand%20collaborations%20to%20sustain%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20evolution%20may%20mean%20some%20don't%20view%20influencers%20as%20relatable%20as%20they%20once%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meltwater.com%2Fen%2Fblog%2Finfluencer-fatigue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%20from%20Meltwater%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20online%20media%20monitoring%20company%2C%20referred%20to%20this%20perceived%20lack%20of%20authenticity%20as%20%26quot%3Binfluencer%20fatigue%26quot%3B%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20social%20media%20users%20wanted%20%26quot%3Breal%2C%20unstaged%20content%20to%20engage%20with%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInfluencers%20may%20be%20losing%20their%20command%20over%20Gen%20Z%20in%20particular%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Finfluencer-fatigue-real-heres-why-195348658.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYahoo%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Data%20shared%20with%20the%20outlet%20from%20a%20YPulse%20study%20found%20that%2045%25%20of%2013%20to%2022-year-old%20respondents%20felt%20influencers%20don't%20have%20the%20sway%20they%20used%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222033%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Influencers%20at%20the%20beach%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66225d0f49058e669357952f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221475%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInfluencers%20at%20the%20beach%20(stock%20photo).%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Falls%20Commercial%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20influencing%20days%20aren't%20over%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20influencing%20is%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20more%20about%20the%20way%20it's%20done%20is%20evolving%2C%20and%20only%20creators%20who%20understand%20this%20will%20be%20successful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finfluencermarketinghub.com%2Finfluencer-marketing-benchmark-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20report%20from%20Influencer%20Marketing%20Hub%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%20found%20there%20was%20a%20strong%20preference%20from%20brands%20to%20work%20with%20small%20nano-%20and%20micro-influencers%20due%20to%20their%20higher%20engagement%20rate%20and%20the%20trust%20built%20with%20their%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESophie%20Wood%2C%20the%20director%20of%20strategy%20at%20influencer%20marketing%20agency%20Fohr%2C%20told%20BI%20the%20influencer%20bubble%20hasn't%20burst%2C%20it's%20just%20changing.%20Deinfluencing%20in%20itself%20is%20influencing%2C%20she%20said%2C%20just%20in%20a%20different%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decade%20ago%2C%20bloggers%20were%20the%20new%2C%20shiny%20type%20of%20celebrity%20that%20everyone%20wanted%20a%20piece%20of.%20Then%20the%20influencer%20boom%20happened%2C%20YouTube%20took%20off%2C%20TikTok%20was%20created%2C%20and%20now%20millions%20of%20people%20can%20be%20given%20that%20label.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmart%20creators%20are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20keep%20their%20communities%20thriving%2C%20such%20as%20joining%20platforms%20such%20as%20Substack%20to%20give%20a%20section%20of%20their%20loyal%20fans%20a%20more%20intimate%20look%20into%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20people%20who%20actually%20have%20something%20different%20to%20say%2C%26quot%3B%20Wood%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHannah%20Witton%2C%20a%20YouTuber%20who%20has%20been%20making%20content%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20for%20example%2C%20moved%20away%20from%20YouTube%20last%20year%20to%20Patreon%2C%20and%20many%20of%20her%20subscribers%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20BI%20influencers%2C%20like%20everyone%2C%20will%20change%20over%20time.%20It's%20hard%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Brelatable%26quot%3B%20to%20everyone%2C%20but%20the%20way%20to%20keep%20followers%20happy%20is%20for%20influencers%20to%20continue%20sharing%20things%20authentically%2C%20even%20as%20their%20interests%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20key%20is%20to%20be%20honest%20about%20changes%20and%20take%20your%20audience%20along%20for%20the%20ride%2C%26quot%3B%20Witton%20said.%20%26quot%3BNaturally%2C%20some%20people%20will%20fall%20off%2C%20but%20many%20will%20stay%2C%20and%20new%20people%20will%20always%20come.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20more%20niche%20communities%2C%20fans%20are%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20see%20the%20influencers%20they%20love%20making%20money%20and%20recommending%20products%2C%20Wood%20said.%20It's%20not%20that%20ads%20are%20bad%2C%20she%20said%2C%20you%20just%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20it%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20proud%20of%20their%20influencer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20like%2C%20get%20your%20bag.%20I%20love%20this%20ad.%20You%20make%20the%20best%20ads.%20That%20is%20the%20golden%20standard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EViewers%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20lied%20to%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETransparency%20is%20really%20important%2C%20as%20some%20influencers%20have%20come%20under%20fire%20recently%20for%20not%20being%20honest%20and%20open%20about%20ads%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yahoo.com%2Flifestyle%2Ftiktok-creator-accused-of-lashlighting-beauty-fans-with-allegedly-misleading-review-there-is-no-disputing-that-she-used-fake-lashes-200923394.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20disclosing%20that%20they%20were%20paid%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20promote%20certain%20products%20or%20trying%20to%20hide%20the%20disclosure%20hashtags%20behind%20the%20video's%20caption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAudiences%20are%20very%20smart%20and%20I%20think%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20feel%20duped%2C%26quot%3B%20Wood%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20going%20to%20be%20like%2C%20this%20influencer%20thinks%20I'm%20dumb%20to%20believe%20this%20ad%20when%20I%20know%20that%20this%20is%20not%20something%20she%20would%20create.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJessica%20Dante%2C%20an%20influencer%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Love%20and%20London%2C%20agreed%20that%20trust%20dwindles%20when%20viewers%20see%20something%20they%20perceive%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmoney%20grab.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20believes%20people%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Brelatability%26quot%3B%20a%20little%20too%20much%2C%20but%20that%20people%20look%20for%20honesty%20and%20integrity%20in%20whatever%20they%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20TikTok%20has%20enabled%20people%20to%20go%20viral%20for%20something%20that%20maybe%20isn't%20authentic%20or%20true%2C%20this%20is%20especially%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20why%20influencers%20are%20oft