0whole%20thing%20vexed%20me%20enough%20that%20I%20started%20to%20really%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Enotice%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-small-businesses-get-more-customer-reviews-use-feedback-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecustomer%20satisfaction%20surveys%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20as%20I'm%20sure%20you've%20seen%2C%20they%20are%20%3Cem%3Eeverywhere%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20seems%20like%20every%20interaction%20I%20have%20with%20a%20money-involving%20organization%20also%20comes%20with%20a%20polite%20request%20for%20my%20feedback.%20A%20restaurant.%20A%20hotel.%20A%20shop.%20The%20insurance%20company%20that%20wasted%20my%20time.%20Every%20time%20I%20buy%20something%20or%20interact%20with%20someone%3A%20another%20survey.%20While%20I%20was%20pitching%20this%20story%20to%20my%20editor%2C%20his%20email%20dinged.%20A%20survey!%20How'd%20we%20do%3F%20How%20long%20was%20your%20wait%20time%3F%20How%20satisfied%20were%20you%20with%20the%20knowledge%20and%20professionalism%20of%20the%20salesperson%20who%20served%20you%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20time%20I'm%20not%20asked%20to%20evaluate%20the%20%3Cem%3Equality%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20a%20product%20or%20service.%20I'm%20asked%20to%20evaluate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fikea-holding-raves-new-customer-retail-experience-expands-us-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20meta-consumption%20that%20drives%20our%20hyperactive%20service%20economy.%20A%20tsunami%20of%20surveys%20has%20turned%20us%20all%20into%20optimization%20analysts%20for%20multibillion-dollar%20companies.%20Bad%20enough%20I'm%20providing%20free%20labor%20to%20help%20a%20transnational%20corporation%20improve%20its%20share%20price%20or%20%26quot%3Bevaluate%26quot%3B%20a%20low-paid%2C%20overworked%2C%20nonunion%20employee.%20It's%20more%20than%20annoying.%20I'm%20starting%20to%20suspect%20it's%20unethical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20just%20my%20imagination.%20We're%20all%20getting%20more%20requests%20for%20feedback.%20Global%20spending%20on%20market%20research%20has%20doubled%20since%202016%2C%20to%20more%20than%20%2480%20billion%20a%20year.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20that%20money%20is%20doled%20out%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20a%20fifth%20of%20it%20%E2%80%94%20%2416%20billion!%20%E2%80%94%20is%20devoted%20to%20customer%20surveys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%20the%20experience%20of%20Qualtrics%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20survey-data%20companies.%20In%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20firm%20has%20analyzed%201.6%20billion%20survey%20responses.%20That's%20a%204%25%20increase%20over%20the%20prior%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20responses%20for%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024%20were%2010%25%20above%20what%20Qualtrics%20projected.%20Its%20analysis%20of%20%26quot%3Bnon-structured%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20to%20say%20customer-service%20phone%20calls%20and%20online%20chatter%2C%20hit%202%20billion%20conversations%20last%20year.%20This%20year%20the%20company%20projects%20an%20increase%20of%2062%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20are%20there%20suddenly%20so%20many%20surveys%3F%20Because%20people%20have%20so%20many%20options%20today%20that%20they're%20not%20bothering%20to%20complain%20when%20something%20sucks.%20They%20just%20move%20on%20to%20a%20different%2C%20equally%20accessible%20website.%20A%20company%20pisses%20them%20off%20or%20disappoints%20them%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Epoof!%20%3C%2Fem%3EThey're%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20customer%20has%20a%20poor%20experience%2C%2010%25%20fewer%20of%20them%20are%20telling%20the%20company%20about%20it%20than%20they%20did%20in%202021%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brad%20Anderson%2C%20the%20president%20of%20product%20and%20engineering%20at%20Qualtrics.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20happening%20is%20they're%20just%20switching.%26quot%3B%20So%20companies%20are%20using%20surveys%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20hang%20on%20to%20those%20unloyal%20customers.%20After%20all%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eit's%20way%20more%20expensive%20to%20acquire%20a%20new%20customer%20than%20keep%20an%20old%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tricky%20part%20is%20marketing%20research%20has%20shown%20that%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20objective%20quality%20of%20a%20product%2C%20its%20nominal%20goodness%2C%20matters%20less%20than%20whether%20it%20meets%20customer%20expectations.%20%26quot%3BQuality%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.emerald.com%2Finsight%2Fcontent%2Fdoi%2F10.1108%2F00251740310457641%2Ffull%2Fhtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresearch%20paper%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20put%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20what%20the%20customer%20says%20it%20is.%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1177%2F002224378001700405%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECustomer%20satisfaction%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20correlates%20with%20profitability%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1509%2Fjmkg.68.4.172.42723%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewith%20share%20price%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ama.org%2Fcustomer-satisfaction-an-organizing-framework-for-strategy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewith%20success%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20to%20get%20all%20philosophical%20for%20a%20moment%2C%20what%20even%20is%20%3Cem%3Esatisfaction%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20anyway%3F%20People%20tried%20for%20decades%20to%20figure%20that%20out.%20Then%2C%20in%202004%2C%20a%20Bain%20consultant%20named%20Fred%20Reichheld%20came%20up%20with%20an%20answer.%20He%20called%20it%20the%20Net%20Promoter%20Score.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20tell%20you%20what%20that%20is%2C%20let%20me%20ask%20you%20a%20question%3A%20On%20a%20scale%20of%201%20to%2010%2C%20how%20likely%20would%20you%20be%20to%20recommend%20this%20article%20to%20someone%20else%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20it.%20That's%20what%20the%20Net%20Promoter%20Score%20does.%20If%20you'd%20recommend%20something%20to%20someone%20else%2C%20it%20has%20by%20definition%20satisfied%20you.%20Mystery%20solved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NPS%20came%20along%20at%20the%20same%20time%20as%20the%20widening%20use%20of%20the%20internet%20and%20social%20media%2C%20which%20made%20it%20%3Cem%3Every%20%3C%2Fem%3Eeasy%20to%20ask%20about.%20Phone%20calls%2C%20snail%20mail%20%E2%80%94%20that%20stuff%20is%20time-consuming%20and%20expensive.%20But%20surveys%20sent%20via%20email%20and%20text%20are%20fast%20and%20cheap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20American%20marketing%2C%20NPS%20became%20an%20unstoppable%20craze.%20Other%20metrics%20followed%3A%20the%20Customer%20Satisfaction%20Score%2C%20the%20Customer%20Effort%20Score%2C%20measurements%20of%20the%20entire%20Customer%20Experience.%20A%20survey%2C%20or%20monitoring%20calls%20to%20customer%20service%2C%20could%20reveal%20loyalty%2C%20intent%20to%20buy%20again%2C%20the%20specific%20parts%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bcustomer%20journey%26quot%3B%20that%20were%20most%20pleasant.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20choose%20based%20on%20objective%20quality%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nick%20Lee%2C%20a%20marketing%20professor%20at%20the%20Warwick%20Business%20School.%20%26quot%3BValue%20is%20added%20by%20way%20more%20than%20what%20we%20would%20call%20objective%20product%20features.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20so-called%20sharing%20economy%2C%20customer%20surveys%20were%20all-powerful.%20They%20went%20both%20ways%3A%20Suddenly%2C%20Uber%20drivers%20%3Cem%3Eand%20%3C%2Fem%3EUber%20riders%20both%20had%20%3Ca%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-drivers-five-star-rider-rating-tips-friends-wait-bags-2023-3%5C%22%3Estar%20ratings%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20care%20about.%20Customer%20surveys%20were%20going%20to%20fix%20asymmetrical%20marketplace%20information.%20But%20of%20course%2C%20the%20whole%20thing%20was%20frothier%20than%20a%20five-star%20milkshake.%20By%20the%20late%202010s%20it%20was%20becoming%20clear%20that%20all%20those%20reviews%20and%20ratings%20were%20getting%20less%20useful%20over%20time.%20They%20were%20subject%2C%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw25857%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereputation%20inflation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Eventually%20everything%20gets%20four%20stars%20out%20of%20five.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20glut%20of%20customer%20surveys%20has%20created%20an%20additional%20problem%20for%20marketers.%20Email%20surveys%20are%20like%20the%20robocalls%20of%20old%3A%20You%20hit%20delete%20without%20even%20looking%20at%20them.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20receive%20so%20many%20survey%20requests%20that%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20refuse%20to%20participate%20in%20any%20survey%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20James%20Wagner%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan's%20Institute%20for%20Social%20Research.%20It's%20called%20oversurveying%2C%20and%20it%20makes%20people%20%3Ca%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0289695%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eless%20likely%20to%20respond%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Which%20means%20that%2C%20for%20statistical%20validity%2C%20companies%20have%20to%20send%20out%20more%20surveys.%20Which%20lowers%20the%20response%20rate%20even%20further%2C%20which%20means%20that%20companies%20have%20to%20send%20out%20yet%20more%20surveys%2C%20in%20a%20never-ending%20doom%20loop.%20On%20a%20scale%20of%201%20to%205%2C%20customer%20satisfaction%20with%20customer-satisfaction%20surveys%20is%20headed%20to%20zero.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20nobody's%20even%20sure%20these%20surveys%20are%20%3Ca%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsloanreview.mit.edu%2Farticle%2Fminding-the-analytics-gap%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emeasuring%20the%20right%20thing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BCompanies%20regularly%20collect%20customer-satisfaction%20measures%2C%20Net%20Promoter%20Scores%2C%20things%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Christine%20Moorman%2C%20a%20business-administration%20professor%20at%20Duke%20University%20who%20heads%20up%20a%20semiannual%20survey%20of%20hundreds%20of%20chief%20marketing%20officers.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%20the%20question%20is%20what%20do%20they%20do%20with%20it%2C%20and%20to%20what%20strategic%20ends%3F%20Most%20of%20them%20are%20doing%20it%20out%20of%20habit%2C%20not%20because%20they're%20thinking%20about%20the%20larger%20strategic%20questions%20they%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20survey%20companies%20don't%20just%20dump%20a%20giant%20Excel%20spreadsheet%20on%20their%20clients%20and%20send%20them%20an%20invoice.%20They%20offer%20sophisticated%20analyses%20of%20the%20data%20they%20collect.%20But%20unless%20those%20numbers%20are%20tied%20to%20possible%20changes%20the%20client%20might%20make%2C%20what's%20the%20point%3F%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20huge%20arms%20race%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Lee%2C%20the%20Warwick%20marketing%20prof.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20give%20me%20more%20data%20rather%20than%20less%20data%2C%20I%20want%20more%20data.%20But%20the%20business%20model%20as%20to%20whether%20that%20data%20is%20valuable%2C%20it's%20sometimes%20questionable.%20Because%20people%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20the%20data%2C%20and%20they%20let%20the%20agency%20tell%20them%20what%20it%20says.%26quot%3B%20Just%20because%20a%20company%20gets%20a%20bunch%20of%20survey%20results%20doesn't%20mean%20it%20knows%20what%20to%20do%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomer%20surveys%20aren't%20just%20bad%20for%20companies.%20After%20reading%20the%20copious%20research%20on%20how%20surveys%20are%20actually%20used%2C%20I've%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20they're%20even%20%3Cem%3Eworse%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20us%2C%20the%20oversurveyed%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20time%20a%20scientist%20wants%20to%20do%20research%20involving%20humans%2C%20it's%20a%20whole%20thing.%20That%20always%20comes%20with%20risks%2C%20from%20exposing%20people%20to%20an%20untested%20drug%20to%20simply%20wasting%20their%20time.%20To%20get%20approved%20by%20an%20Institutional%20Review%20Board%2C%20the%20potential%20results%20have%20to%20be%20worth%20the%20risks%2C%20to%20provide%20some%20benefit%20to%20humanity.%20That's%20called%20%26quot%3Bequipoise.%26quot%3B%20And%20if%20a%20proposed%20experiment%20on%20living%20things%20doesn't%20have%20it%2C%20you%20ain't%20supposed%20to%20do%20the%20experiment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20customer%20surveys%20should%20be%20evaluated%20for%20equipoise.%20If%20the%20companies%20actually%20use%20the%20data%20to%20improve%20a%20product%20or%20experience%2C%20that's%20good%20for%20us%20subjects.%20But%20what%20if%20it's%20used%20only%20to%20improve%20the%20company's%20share%20value%20or%20profitability%3F%20Or%20to%20discipline%20or%20fire%20employees%3F%20That%20only%20helps%20the%20company.%20And%20that%20doesn't%20even%20take%20into%20account%20whether%20I%2C%20the%20surveyed%20one%2C%20gave%20my%20consent%20for%20data%20I%20provided%20to%20be%20used%20in%20that%20way%20%E2%80%94%20a%20key%20to%20ethical%20research.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20we%20should%20have%20to%20pre-tell%20people%20what%20we're%20going%20to%20do%20with%20the%20data%20before%20we%20get%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20would%20be%20a%20way%20to%20stop%20companies%20from%20doing%20it%20indiscriminately.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20knows%20that's%20a%20nonstarter.%20%26quot%3BWe'd%20be%20adding%20bureaucracy%20into%20the%20system.%20Never%20a%20popular%20thing%20to%20do%20with%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorse%2C%20for%20vast%20swaths%20of%20services%2C%20you%20and%20I%20are%20the%20%3Cem%3Elast%3C%2Fem%3E%20people%20anyone%20should%20be%20soliciting%20opinions%20from.%20Things%20like%20doctor%20visits%2C%20legal%20services%2C%20or%20school%20classes%20are%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20hard%20for%20the%20user%20to%20evaluate%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20ask%20for%20customer%20feedback%20on%20these%20things%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20for%20a%20customer%20to%20give%20you%20immediate%20feedback%2C%20because%20a%20customer%20doesn't%20know%20what%20quality%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20yet.%26quot%3B%20The%20college%20class%20you%20hated%20because%20it%20was%20hard%2C%20and%20at%208%20a.m.%2C%20might%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20your%20favorite%20academic%20memory%20and%20the%20foundation%20for%20your%20professional%20skill%20set%2015%20years%20later.%20Whether%20a%20visit%20to%20the%20mechanic%20was%20pleasant%20doesn't%20tell%20you%20how%20well%20they%20fixed%20your%20car.%20You%20have%20to%20drive%20around%20with%20your%20new%20drive%20shaft%20awhile%20to%20know%20whether%20you%20got%20shafted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20has%20unpublished%20data%2C%20which%20hasn't%20been%20peer-reviewed%2C%20comparing%20hospital%20performance%20in%20Britain's%20National%20Health%20Service%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewith%20surveys%20of%20both%20patients%20and%20employees.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20surprising%20that%20the%20best%20hospitals%20have%20the%20best%20patient%20feedback%20and%20best%20worker%20feedback%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20But%20what%20%3Cem%3Eis%20%3C%2Fem%3Esurprising%20is%20that%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eworker%20feedback%2C%20not%20customer%20responses%2C%20correlates%20most%20closely%20with%20quality.%20Users%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20aren't%20very%20good%20at%20telling%20what's%20what.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20know%20what%20%3Cem%3Eis%20%3C%2Fem%3Egood%20at%20sorting%20through%20tons%20of%20data%3F%20Artificial%20intelligence.%20As%20email%20surveys%20get%20lower%20and%20lower%20response%20rates%2C%20consumer%20marketing%20companies%20have%20begun%20to%20tout%20their%20acumen%20at%20applying%20AI%20to%20the%20unstructured%20verbiage%20of%20online%20reviews%2C%20social-media%20posts%2C%20and%20call-center%20transcripts.%20Maybe%20these%20new%20tools%2C%20based%20on%20large%20language%20models%2C%20will%20be%20able%20to%20coax%20better%20responses%20from%20oversurveyed%20consumers.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20ability%20to%20be%20able%20to%20detect%20when%20there's%20a%20low-quality%20answer%20and%20come%20back%20and%20ask%20the%20customer%20for%20more%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20ask%20the%20second%20question%2C%2040%25%20of%20the%20time%20the%20customer%20engages%20and%20provides%20more%20data.%20The%20number%20of%20syllables%20in%20the%20second%20response%20increases%20by%209x.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20if%20I%20get%20a%20callback%20from%20a%20customer-survey%20robot%2C%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20most%20of%20those%20additional%20syllables%20will%20be%20profane.%20How%20will%20I%20rate%20my%20experience%20getting%20interviewed%20by%20an%20AI%3F%20It%20might%20get%20more%20actionable%20data%20out%20of%20me%20than%20that%20email%20from%20my%20kid's%20allergist%20did.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20I'm%20pretty%20sure%20I%20won't%20recommend%20it%20to%20a%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomer-satisfaction-surveys-scourge-annoying-ratings-email-marketing-research-workers-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713777781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6622776320b15f0ff4298038%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomer-satisfaction-surveys-scourge-annoying-ratings-email-marketing-research-workers-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Why%20your%20inbox%20is%20overflowing%20with%20questionnaires%20asking%20you%20to%20rate%20your%20exper