0Buyer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20India%20have%20typically%20vied%20over%20the%20title%20of%20world's%20biggest%20buyer.%20But%20that%20shifted%20last%20year%20as%20Chinese%20consumption%20of%20jewelry%2C%20bars%20and%20coins%20swelled%20to%20record%20levels.%20China's%20gold%20jewelry%20demand%20rose%2010%25%20while%20India's%20fell%206%25.%20Chinese%20bar%20and%20coin%20investments%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20surged%2028%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20there's%20still%20room%20for%20demand%20to%20grow%2C%20said%20Philip%20Klapwijk%2C%20managing%20director%20of%20Hong%20Kong-based%20consultant%20Precious%20Metals%20Insights%20Ltd.%20Amid%20limited%20investment%20options%20in%20China%2C%20the%20protracted%20crisis%20in%20its%20property%20sector%2C%20volatile%20stock%20markets%20and%20a%20weakening%20yuan%20are%20all%20driving%20money%20to%20assets%20that%20are%20perceived%20to%20be%20safer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20weight%20of%20money%20available%20under%20these%20circumstances%20for%20an%20asset%20like%20gold%20-%20and%20actually%20for%20new%20buyers%20to%20come%20in%20-%20is%20pretty%20considerable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20isn't%20much%20alternative%20in%20China.%20With%20exchange%20controls%20and%20capital%20controls%2C%20you%20can't%20just%20look%20at%20other%20markets%20to%20put%20your%20money%20into.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImports%20Jump%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20China%20mines%20more%20gold%20than%20any%20other%20country%2C%20it%20still%20needs%20to%20import%20a%20lot%20and%20the%20quantities%20are%20getting%20larger.%20In%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20overseas%20purchases%20totaled%20over%202%2C800%20tons%20-%20more%20than%20all%20of%20the%20metal%20that%20backs%20exchange-traded%20funds%20around%20the%20world%2C%20or%20about%20a%20third%20of%20the%20stockpiles%20held%20by%20the%20US%20Federal%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20the%20pace%20of%20shipments%20has%20accelerated%20lately.%20Imports%20surged%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20China's%20Lunar%20New%20Year%2C%20a%20peak%20season%20for%20gifts%2C%20and%20over%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20the%20year%20are%2034%25%20higher%20than%20they%20were%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECentral%20Bank%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20People's%20Bank%20of%20China%20has%20been%20on%20a%20buying%20spree%20for%2017%20straight%20months%2C%20its%20longest-ever%20run%20of%20purchases%2C%20as%20it%20looks%20to%20diversify%20its%20reserves%20away%20from%20the%20dollar%20and%20hedge%20against%20currency%20depreciation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20keenest%20buyer%20among%20a%20number%20central%20banks%20that%20are%20favoring%20gold.%20The%20official%20sector%20snapped%20up%20near-record%20levels%20of%20the%20precious%20metal%20last%20year%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20keep%20purchases%20elevated%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShanghai%20Premium%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20indicative%20of%20gold's%20allure%20that%20Chinese%20demand%20remains%20so%20buoyant%2C%20despite%20record%20prices%20and%20a%20weaker%20yuan%20that%20robs%20buyers%20of%20purchasing%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20major%20importer%2C%20gold%20buyers%20in%20China%20often%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20premium%20over%20international%20prices.%20That%20jumped%20to%20%2489%20an%20ounce%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20month.%20The%20average%20over%20the%20past%20year%20is%20%2435%20versus%20a%20historical%20average%20of%20just%20%247.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20sure%2C%20sky-high%20prices%20are%20likely%20to%20temper%20some%20enthusiasm%20for%20bullion%2C%20but%20the%20market's%20proving%20to%20be%20unusually%20resilient.%20Chinese%20consumers%20have%20typically%20snapped%20up%20gold%20when%20prices%20drop%2C%20which%20has%20helped%20establish%20a%20floor%20for%20the%20market%20during%20times%20of%20weakness.%20Not%20so%20this%20time%2C%20as%20China's%20appetite%20is%20helping%20to%20prop%20up%20prices%20at%20much%20higher%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20suggests%20the%20rally%20is%20sustainable%20and%20gold%20buyers%20everywhere%20should%20be%20comforted%20by%20China's%20booming%20demand%2C%20said%20Nikos%20Kavalis%2C%20managing%20director%20at%20consultancy%20Metals%20Focus%20Ltd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20authorities%2C%20which%20can%20be%20quite%20hostile%20to%20market%20speculation%2C%20are%20less%20sanguine.%20State%20media%20have%20warned%20investors%20to%20be%20cautious%20in%20chasing%20the%20rally%2C%20while%20both%20the%20Shanghai%20Gold%20Exchange%20and%20Shanghai%20Futures%20Exchange%20have%20raised%20margin%20requirements%20on%20some%20contracts%20to%20snuff%20out%20excessive%20risk-taking.%20SHFE's%20move%20followed%20a%20surge%20in%20daily%20trading%20volumes%20to%20a%20five-year%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EETF%20Flows%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20less%20frenetic%20way%20to%20invest%20in%20gold%20is%20via%20exchange-traded%20funds.%20Money%20has%20flowed%20into%20gold%20ETFs%20in%20mainland%20China%20during%20almost%20every%20month%20since%20June%2C%20according%20to%20Bloomberg%20Intelligence.%20That%20compares%20with%20chunky%20outflows%20in%20gold%20funds%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20influx%20of%20money%20has%20totaled%20%241.3%20billion%20so%20far%20this%20year%2C%20compared%20with%20%244%20billion%20in%20outflows%20from%20funds%20overseas.%20Restrictions%20on%20investing%20in%20China%20are%20again%20a%20factor%20here%2C%20given%20the%20fewer%20options%20for%20Chinese%20beyond%20domestic%20property%20and%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChinese%20demand%20could%20continue%20to%20rise%20as%20investors%20look%20to%20diversify%20their%20holdings%20with%20commodities%2C%20BI%20analyst%20Rebecca%20Sin%20said%20in%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20Wire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChile%20imposed%20temporary%20anti-dumping%20tariffs%20on%20Chinese%20steel%20products%20used%20in%20the%20country's%20mining%20industry%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20support%20faltering%20local%20producers.%20The%20move%20pushed%20Cap%20SA%20to%20reverse%20a%20decision%20to%20wind%20down%20its%20steel%20mills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20most-promising%20industries%20are%20facing%20a%20growing%20threat%20of%20trade%20restrictions%20from%20Western%20governments%2C%20blurring%20the%20outlook%20for%20stocks%20that%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20fuel%20the%20nation's%20market%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Beijing%20already%20becoming%20a%20top%20target%20in%20the%20US%20election%20campaign%2C%20President%20Xi%20Jinping's%20government%20is%20resisting%20any%20move%20that%20could%20backfire%20on%20the%20world's%20second-largest%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20introduce%20a%20raft%20of%20tariffs%20and%20restrictions%20to%20protect%20domestic%20industries%2C%20you'd%20better%20make%20sure%20there%20are%20some%20around%20to%20protect.%20That's%20a%20major%20problem%20with%20the%20US%20decision%20to%20treat%20China's%20clean%20technology%20leadership%20as%20grounds%20for%20a%20trade%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713776880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fnu53mldg_gold_625x300_22_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchina-is-front-and-center-of-golds-record-breaking-rally-5496730%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China%2C%20the%20world's%20biggest%20producer%20and%20consumer%20of%20the%20precious%20metal%2C%20is%20front%20and%20center%20of%20the%20extraordinary%20ascent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchina-is-front-and-center-of-golds-record-breaking-rally-5496730%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Poll%20Sops%3A%20Why%20Voters%20Must%20Question%20Their%20Long-Term%20Feasibility%20Too%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-08%2Findia-crowd-generic-istock_650x400_61503730268.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Finternational-monetary-fund-imf%5C%22%3EInternational%20Monetary%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20(IMF)%20released%20its%20latest%20Fiscal%20Monitor%20report%2C%20which%20discusses%20%26quot%3Bfiscal%20policy%20in%20the%20great%20election%20year%26quot%3B.%20%C2%A0A%20previous%20edition%20of%20the%20Fiscal%20Monitor%20had%20highlighted%20a%20significant%20policy%20'trilemma'%20stemming%20from...%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESpending%20demands%20on%20national%20budgets%20due%20to%20wages%2C%20pensions%2C%20health%20care%2C%20industrial%20strategies%2C%20environmental%20concerns%2C%20defence%2C%20and%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWidespread%20political%20reluctance%20to%20increase%20taxes%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20imperative%20to%20manage%20debt%20and%20deficits%20to%20ensure%20fiscal%20stability%20and%20financial%20sustainability%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20escalating%20interest%20rates%20and%20dimming%20medium-term%20growth%20forecasts%20complicate%20debt%20management.%20However%2C%20according%20to%20the%20IMF%2C%20this%20trilemma%20would%20exert%20a%20heavy%20influence%20globally%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F2024-a-defining-year-for-global-democracy-with-elections-in-over-64-countries-5012806%5C%22%3E88%20countries%20go%20to%20polls%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%20The%20IMF%20has%20warned%20against%20fiscal%20slippages%20this%20election%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETailored%20Policies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20dearth%20of%20evidence%20for%20such%20slippages.%20The%20%3Cem%3EPolitical%20Business%20Cycle%20Theory%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20William%20Nordhaus%20(1975)%20suggests%20that%20elected%20officials%20may%20manipulate%20economic%20policies%20to%20engineer%20favourable%20economic%20outcomes%20around%20election%20time.%20In%20particular%2C%20it%20posits%20that%20governments%20tend%20to%20increase%20public%20spending%20and%20cut%20taxes%20to%20boost%20economic%20activity%20and%20improve%20their%20electoral%20prospects%2C%20even%20if%20this%20may%20lead%20to%20larger%20deficits%20and%20greater%20long-term%20debt%20burdens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20India%20has%20diverged%20from%20this%20typical%20scenario%20in%20recent%20years.%20Instead%20of%20succumbing%20to%20the%20temptation%20of%20interim%20budgets%20that%20primarily%20focus%20on%20short-term%20gains%20and%20securing%20votes%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F2024-lok-sabha-elections-free-electricity-healthcare-across-india-arvind-kejriwals-poll-promises-5344586%5C%22%3Enew%20subsidies%20and%20other%20financial%20incentives%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recent%20approaches%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20have%20prioritised%20long-term%20fiscal%20discipline%20over%20populist%20measures%2C%20highlighting%20a%20decade%20of%20economic%20stability%20and%20empowerment.%20This%20marks%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20predicted%20bias%20towards%20fiscal%20slippages%20in%20election%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20fiscal%20sustainability%20in%20welfare%20states%20hinges%20significantly%20on%20the%20notion%20of%20fiscal%20space%2C%20which%20Peter%20S.%20Heller%20defined%20as%20the%20ability%20of%20a%20government%20to%20allocate%20resources%20for%20specific%20goals%20without%20compromising%20on%20financial%20health.%20The%20challenge%20of%20securing%20such%20a%20fiscal%20space%20is%20multifaceted.%20It%20requires%20strategies%20to%20generate%20the%20necessary%20funds%20to%20meet%20social%20obligations%20while%20simultaneously%20ensuring%20that%20these%20financial%20mechanisms%20do%20not%20stifle%20economic%20growth%20or%20disrupt%20fiscal%20stability.%20Authors%20like%20Marcel%20(2014)%20and%20Harris%20(2013)%2C%20along%20with%20Ortiz%20et%20al.%20in%20multiple%20works%20emphasise%20the%20balance%20required%20to%20manage%20welfare%20expenditures%20and%20revenue%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuestioning%20Fiscal%20Proposals%20Too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20literature%20on%20fiscal%20slippage%20before%20elections%2C%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20more%20focus%20on%20how%20fiscal%20sustainability%20is%20affected%20after%20elections%20when%20a%20new%20government%20is%20installed.%20Often%2C%20a%20new%20government%20may%20become%20fiscally%20imprudent%20in%20its%20quest%20to%20deliver%20on%20pre-poll%20promises%2C%20some%20of%20which%20might%20be%20financially%20ill-judged.%20Such%20promises%20often%20crowd%20out%20capital%20expenditure%2C%20which%20has%20a%20higher%20multiplier%20effect%20on%20the%20economy%20and%20people's%20overall%20well-being.%20One%20example%20of%20this%20is%20poll%20promises%20made%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fkarnataka-budget-5-guarantees-and-their-relevance-for-congress-4187424%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20Karnataka%20government%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20February%2C%20an%20economic%20adviser%20to%20the%20state's%20chief%20minister%20claimed%20that%20%26quot%3Bfive%20poll%20guarantees%20is%20imposing%20a%20huge%20financial%20burden%20on%20the%20exchequer%20and%20exerting%20significant%20pressure%20on%20the%20state's%20economy%26quot%3B.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThis%20brings%20us%20to%20a%20wider%20debate%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fex-rbi-chief-demands-centres-white-paper-on-political-parties-freebies-5488812%5C%22%3Eempowerment%20vs.%20freebies%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20social%20policy.%20While%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20cash%20and%20subsidies%20are%20necessary%2C%20political%20parties%20and%20governments%20should%20think%20more%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Fcan-india-afford-poll-freebies-and-wealth-redistribution-economist-kv-subramanian-explains-777046%5C%22%3Eempowering%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20just%20doling%20out%20freebies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEntitlement%20vs%20Empowerment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20merely%20providing%20cash%2C%20empowering%20individuals%20through%20social%20policy%20can%20enhance%20personal%20agency%20and%20reduce%20the%20fiscal%20burden%20on%20government%20resources.%20There%20already%20is%20substantial%20theoretical%20and%20empirical%20evidence%20to%20support%20this.%20The%20argument%20draws%20on%20Amartya%20Sen's%20'Capability%20Approach'%2C%20which%20emphasises%20giving%20people%20the%20means%20to%20pursue%20their%20conception%20of%20a%20good%20life.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnEsther%20Duflo%20and%20Abhijit%20Banerjee's%20work%20found%20that%20initiatives%20aimed%20at%20enhancing%20the%20skills%20and%20productive%20capabilities%20of%20the%20poor%20(like%20vocational%20training%20and%20microfinance)%20can%20lead%20to%20sustained%20economic%20improvements%20and%20reduced%20reliance%20on%20state-provided%20benefits.%C2%A0This%20further%20supports%20the%20case%20for%20promoting%20empowerment%20over%20entitlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intersection%20of%20entitlement%20and%20empowerment%20is%20crucial%20for%20sustainable%20development.%20While%20entitlement%20lays%20the%20foundation%20by%20establishing%20legal%20rights%20and%20frameworks%20that%20recognise%20and%20protect%20women's%20rights%2C%20empowerment%20ensures%20that%20women%20have%20the%20practical%20means%20to%20utilise%20these%20rights%20to%20improve%20their%20lives%20and%20impact%20their%20communities.%20Duflo's%20research%2C%20for%20example%2C%20illustrates%20how%20this%20can%20bring%20about%20improved%20development%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Perils%20Of%20Macroeconomic%20Instability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFreebies%20announced%20by%20several%20parties%20during%20the%20elections%20are%20expansionary.%20They%20might%20widen%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20sharply.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20they%20may%20hurt%20macroeconomic%20stability%20in%20the%20long%20run%20and%20affect%20private%20corporate%20capex%20recovery.%20Macroeconomic%20instability%2C%20marked%20by%20fluctuations%20in%20GDP%2C%20inflation%20rates%20and%20employment%20levels%2C%20directly%20impacts%20government%20budgets%20and%20expenditures.%20During%20economic%20downturns%2C%20reduced%20tax%20revenues%20and%20increased%20demand%20for%20welfare%20programmes%20can%20strain%20public%20finances%2C%20necessitating%20cuts%20in%20other%20areas%20or%20more%20borrowing.%20This%20financial%20pressure%20may%20lead%20to%20reduced%20investments%20in%20critical%20long-term%20social%20programmes%20such%20as%20education%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20social%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20persistent%20instability%20often%20exacerbates%20income%20inequality%2C%20and%20those%20from%20lower%20socioeconomic%20backgrounds%20bear%20the%20brunt%20of%20economic%20downturns.%20This%20widening%20gap%20can%20compel%20policy%20adjustments%20to%20address%20disparities%20through%20measures%20like%20progressive%20taxation%20and%20targeted%20social%20assistance.%20It%20also%20necessitates%20policies%20aimed%20at%20promoting%20social%20cohesion%20and%20inclusive%20growth%20to%20maintain%20political%20and%20social%20stability.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnMoreover%2C%20economic%20volatility%20complicates%20long-term%20planning%20and%20the%20implementation%20of%20social%20policies.%20This%20underlines%20the%20need%20for%20flexibility%20and%20resilience%20in%20policy%20frameworks.%20Health%20and%20educational%20outcomes%20can%20deteriorate%20during%20recessions%20due%20to%20reduced%20spending%2C%20and%20this%20calls%20for%20policies%20that%20can%20adapt%20and%20prioritise%20these%20sectors%20even%20during%20tough%20economic%20times.%20In%20the%20longer%20term%2C%20macroeconomic%20instability%20also%20affects%20demographic%20patterns%20and%20can%20influence%20birth%20rates%20and%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBalancing%20Short-Term%20Gains%20With%20Long-Term%20Feasibility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20thus%20necessary%20to%20judge%20political%20parties%20not%20just%20on%20the%20promises%20they%20make%20but%20also%20on%20the%20fiscal%20plans%20they%20propose%20to%20service%20those%20promises%20sustainably.%20Political%20campaigns%20often%20feature%20a%20plethora%20of%20pledges%20designed%20to%20attract%20various%20voter%20groups.%20Yet%2C%20the%20feasibility%20of%20these%20promises%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20true%20measure%20of%20responsible%20governance%20should%20be%20the%20ability%20of%20a%20party%20to%20articulate%20how%20it%20will%20balance%20short-term%20electoral%20incentives%20with%20the%20long-term%20fiscal%20health%20of%20the%20economy.%20This%20will%20encourage%20the%20evolution%20of%20a%20more%20informed%20electorate%20and%20promote%20policies%20that%20are%20not%20just%20appealing%20in%20the%20short%20run%20but%20also%20beneficial%20and%20sustainable%20in%20the%20long%20term.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E(Bibek%20Debroy%20(%40bibekdebroy)%20is%20Chairman%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%20Aditya%20Sinha%20(%40adityasinha004)%20is%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%2C%20Research%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20views%20of%20the%20authors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713776820000%2C%22visual%22%3A