Fstrong%3Etech%20company%20in%20San%20Francisco%20for%20three%20years%20in%20two%20different%20roles%20%E2%80%94%20first%20in%20an%20HR%20function%20and%20then%20as%20a%20program%20manager%20on%20a%20team%20of%20five%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20into%20my%20second%20role%2C%20I%20was%20placed%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-manager-told-put-workers-pips-got-laid-off-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20improvement%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20(PIP).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20wake-up%20call%20and%20very%20unexpected%2C%20but%20it%20became%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorking%20at%20a%20%3Cstrong%3Etop-tier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20tech%20company%20was%20amazing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20for%20that%20company%20wasn't%20something%20I'd%20always%20envisioned%20for%20myself%2C%20but%20my%20roles%20felt%20purpose-driven%20and%20aligned%20with%20my%20goals%2C%20which%20were%20to%20be%20a%20catalyst%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-programs-america-diversity-equity-inclusion-pushback-how-to-fix-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediversity%20and%20inclusion%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20to%20open%20doors%20into%20tech%20for%20communities%20of%20color.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20a%20very%20direct%2C%20results-oriented%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20excuses%20are%20not%20tolerated%20and%20excellence%20is%20the%20standard.%20This%2C%20combined%20with%20flawless%20execution%20at%20such%20a%20scale%2C%20created%20a%20unique%20vibe%20that%20I%20was%20drawn%20to%20and%20made%20it%20an%20honor%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefore%20I%20was%20placed%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20warning%20signs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20returning%20from%20a%20conference%2C%20I%20was%20told%20that%20a%20senior%20leader%20wasn't%20happy%20with%20my%20demeanor.%20I%20felt%20out%20of%20place%20at%20the%20event%20while%20others%20were%20bonding%2C%20and%20it%20was%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehard%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20me%20to%20fake%20my%20emotions.%20No%20one%20shared%20feedback%20with%20me%20at%20the%20conference%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20hadn't%20been%20present%20mentally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnice-workplace-culture-might-be-red-flag-nyu-professor-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkplace%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20wasn't%20at%20its%20best%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20team%20morale%20was%20lower%20than%20it%20had%20been%20in%20previous%20months.%20I%20felt%20disconnected%20from%20the%20work%20and%20my%20team's%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20HR%20leader%20suggested%20I%20prepare%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-this-is-an-excellent-resume-2013-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20I%20interpreted%20as%20meaning%20I%20could%20get%20fired.%20Instead%2C%20in%20a%20meeting%20soon%20after%2C%20my%20manager%20told%20me%20I%20was%20being%20placed%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurvived-performance-plan-wasnt-worth-hard-work-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20improvement%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20requested%20that%20I%20document%20all%20my%20work%20moving%20forward%2C%20including%20weekly%20action%20items%2C%20meetings%2C%20and%20interactions%20in%20a%20weekly%20report%20tied%20to%20my%20next%20big%20conference%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFear%20and%20shame%20were%20my%20initial%20reactions.%20Taking%20responsibility%20for%20my%20mistakes%20was%20easy%3B%20the%20hard%20part%20was%20not%20dwelling%20on%20my%20disappointment%20or%20beating%20myself%20up%20over%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20shock%20subsided%2C%20I%20gave%20myself%20an%20honest%20self-assessment.%20I%20decided%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20I%20could%20control%20and%20use%20this%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20improve%20my%20communication%2C%20focus%2C%20and%20work%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20tried%20to%20view%20the%20PIP%20as%20an%20opportunity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-career-coaching-side-hustle-earn-extra-money-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecareer%20coach%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20assess%20my%20work%20habits%20and%20uncover%20blind%20spots%20that%20were%20limiting%20my%20productivity%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20overcoming%20procrastination%20and%20understanding%20my%20communication%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20crafted%20a%20plan%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-smart-goals-used-by-managers-worldwide-should-be-consigned-to-history-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESMART%20goals%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20setting%20healthy%20boundaries%2C%20did%20exercises%20to%20help%20me%20navigate%20confrontation%2C%20and%20discussed%20ways%20I%20could%20improve%20task%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20outlined%20in%20the%20PIP%2C%20I%20documented%20my%20progress%20and%20tracked%20my%20wins.%20I%20found%20it%20helpful%20to%20journal%20as%20much%20as%C2%A0I%20could%20each%20day%20and%20write%20down%20things%20I%20was%20proud%20of%20to%20help%20reinforce%20my%20confidence%20and%20sense%20of%20self-worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20prioritized%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetwork-opportunities-work-job-careers-linkedin-social-media-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enetworking%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20building%20relationships.%20I%20volunteered%20for%20projects%2C%20participated%20in%20committees%2C%20and%20met%20with%20colleagues%20in%20different%20departments%20and%20peers%20at%20different%20companies.%20I%20told%20certain%20peers%20I%20was%20close%20with%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20few%20senior%20colleagues%20that%20I%20trusted%20%E2%80%94%20about%20my%20PIP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20PIP%20was%20a%20much-needed%20kick%20in%20the%20butt%2C%20and%20I%20came%20out%20on%20top%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20on%20the%20PIP%20for%20about%20two%20months.%20I%20treated%20it%20like%20a%20challenge%20I%20was%20determined%20to%20overcome%2C%20but%20the%20anxiety%20caused%20significant%20weight%20loss.%20It%20was%20a%20mentally%2C%20emotionally%2C%20and%20physically%20demanding%20experience.%20My%20partner%20at%20the%20time%20noticed%20and%20was%20concerned%20for%20my%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20I%20wasn't%20terminated.%20After%20I%20completed%20the%20project%2C%20my%20manager%20gave%20me%20positive%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20accept%20responsibility%2C%20I%20think%20a%20significant%20factor%20in%20my%20getting%20put%20on%20the%20PIP%20in%20the%20first%20place%20was%20miscommunication%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20alignment%20with%20my%20new%20manager%2C%20whom%20I%20began%20working%20under%20less%20than%20two%20years%20into%20my%20time%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20struggled%20to%20adapt%20to%20department%20restructuring%20and%20didn't%20feel%20adequately%20supported.%20I%20really%20missed%20my%20original%20manager%2C%20who%20was%20a%20great%20mentor%20and%20someone%20I%20trusted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFriction%20with%20my%20new%20manager%20was%20difficult%20to%20overcome%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20new%20manager%20and%20I%20had%20different%20work%20styles%2C%20which%20sometimes%20led%20to%20friction.%20The%20turnaround%20times%20for%20my%20new%20manager's%20deadlines%20were%20aggressive%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I%20missed%20a%20couple%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20them%20joining%20the%20team%2C%20which%20didn't%20set%20the%20right%20impression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20was%20pretty%20lean%20at%20this%20point%2C%20and%20we%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20internal%20organizations%20that%20needed%20stakeholder%20management.%20My%20manager%20instructed%20that%20I%20take%20on%20the%20added%20workload%20in%20addition%20to%20my%20other%20projects%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20feel%20equipped%20to%20do%20this%20effectively.%20It%20felt%20like%20my%20scope%20was%20rapidly%20increasing%2C%20and%20my%20performance%20was%20being%20rigorously%20tied%20to%20a%20new%20set%20of%20key%20metrics%20overnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20that%20this%20is%20what%20can%20happen%20when%20new%20leadership%20comes%20in%20and%20sets%20a%20new%20tone%20for%20a%20team.%20I%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%20the%20abrupt%20shift%20in%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20cope%2C%20I%20leaned%20more%20on%20my%20side%20hustle%2C%20which%20fueled%20me%20creatively%20but%20also%20impacted%20my%20work%20performance%20at%20times.%20Tapping%20more%20into%20my%20side%20business%20while%20enduring%20the%20rocky%20workplace%20culture%20made%20me%20less%20motivated%20to%20go%20the%20extra%20mile%20at%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20now%2C%20I%20understand%20and%20appreciate%20my%20new%20manager's%20changes%20even%20though%20they%20were%20uncomfortable%20at%20the%20time.%20Our%20dynamic%20after%20the%20PIP%20was%20pleasant%2C%20but%20the%20circumstances%20left%20me%20feeling%20confused%20and%C2%A0more%20guarded%20than%C2%A0I%C2%A0wanted%20to%20feel%20when%20reporting%20to%20someone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20PIP%20experience%20ultimately%20left%20me%20feeling%20disheartened%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%20solidified%20the%20reality%20that%20employees%20are%20expendable.%20I%20left%20the%20company%20on%20my%20own%20terms%20about%20two%20months%20after%20my%20PIP%20ended.%20The%20PIP%20wasn't%20the%20sole%20reason%2C%20but%20it%20did%20accelerate%20my%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20a%20new%20job%20at%20another%20company%20as%20a%20program%20manager.%20My%20PIP%20didn't%20come%20up%20in%20my%20interview%20and%20wasn't%20a%20factor%2C%20even%20with%20the%20references%20I%20gave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20PIP%20made%20me%20realize%20the%20importance%20of%20prioritizing%20mental%20health%20and%20personal%20development%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%C2%A0going%20through%20the%20initial%20trauma%20of%20the%20PIP%2C%20I%20learned%20to%20confront%20the%20areas%20of%20my%20life%20that%20needed%20improvement%20so%20I%20could%20perform%20at%20the%20highest%20level%20possible.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20pleasant%20experience%2C%20but%20it%20gave%20me%20a%20clear%20road%20map%20for%20improvement%20and%20lessons%20I%20can%20share%20with%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20PIP%20experience%20also%20solidified%20the%20importance%20of%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-full-time-job-diversify-income-streams-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%20income%20streams%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20highlighting%20the%20vulnerability%20of%20relying%20solely%20on%20a%20salaried%20position.%20I%20continued%20to%20develop%20my%20side%20hustle%2C%20which%20eventually%20became%20my%20current%20full-time%20venture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20I%20navigate%20conflict%20with%20tenacity%20and%20a%20more%20positive%20mindset.%20Instead%20of%20dwelling%20on%20the%20negatives%20when%20things%20go%20sideways%2C%20I%20focus%20on%20the%20skills%20I%20can%20develop%20to%20lead%20to%20a%20better%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-top-tech-company-bounced-back-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713776702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661819283f923f7dab06f240%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-top-tech-company-bounced-back-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20former%20program%20manager%20who%20was%20placed%20on%20a%20PIP%20at%20a%20top%20tech%20company%20says%20their%20initial%20reactions%20were%20fear%20and%20shame.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Robin%20Madell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-top-tech-company-bounced-back-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Many%20cities%20are%20fighting%20the%20urban%20'doom%20loop'%20by%20turning%20empty%20offices%20into%2024%2F7%20social%20districts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20tower%20and%20other%20buildings.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662123b220b15f0ff429126f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20view%20of%20The%20Strat%20Hotel%20%26amp%3B%20Casino%20%26amp%3B%20Tower%20from%20downtown%20Las%20Vegas.%20%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Rose%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENorth%20American%20downtowns%20are%20struggling%20as%20remote%20work%20dominates%20the%20white-collar%20workforce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20University%20of%20Toronto%20study%20shows%20a%20gradual%20uptick%20in%20downtown%20foot%20traffic.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDowntowns%20are%20looking%20to%20transition%20into%20mixed-use%20districts%20and%20ease%20their%20dependence%20on%20offices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20remote%20work%20cements%20its%20grip%20on%20the%20white-collar%20workforce%2C%20North%20American%20downtowns%20are%20working%20to%20fight%20off%20a%20downward%20spiral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20are%20attempting%20the%20transition%20from%20office-only%20districts%20to%20mixed-use%20neighborhoods%20with%20new%20residents%20and%20businesses.%20But%20breathing%20new%20life%20into%20areas%20dominated%20by%20half-empty%20office%20buildings%20is%20proving%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20newly%20updated%20report%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdowntownrecovery.com%2Fcharts%2Ftrends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Toronto%3C%2Fa%3E%20analyzing%20anonymized%20cellphone%20data%20shows%20the%20largest%20North%20American%20downtowns%20have%20generally%20seen%20a%20gradual%20uptick%20in%20foot%20traffic%20over%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20cities%20are%20working%20to%20turn%20vacant%20offices%20into%20homes%2C%20give%20restaurants%20and%20other%20businesses%20tax%20breaks%20to%20move%20downtown%2C%20and%20otherwise%20turn%20office%20districts%20into%20vibrant%20neighborhoods.%20But%20it%20takes%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDowntowns%20are%20going%20through%20this%20painful%20transformation%20to%2024%2F7%20social%20districts%20from%20being%20office%20districts%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Karen%20Chapple%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20School%20of%20Cities%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%20and%20a%20coauthor%20of%20the%20downtown-recovery%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20found%20that%20while%20most%20cities%20had%20seen%20their%20office%20occupancies%20stagnate%2C%20they'd%20seen%20an%20uptick%20in%20nighttime%20and%20weekend%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20a%20really%20striking%20picture%20of%20many%20cities%20where%20weeknights%20and%20weekends%20are%20completely%20back%20to%20normal%2C%20but%20the%20overall%20recovery%20rate%20is%20being%20dragged%20down%20by%20the%20working-hour%20activity%2C%20which%20is%20still%20slow%2C%26quot%3B%20Chapple%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20new%20downtown%20activity%20from%20March%202023%20and%20February%202024%20has%20slowed%20and%20even%20fallen%20in%20some%20cities.%20The%20median%20rate%20of%20change%20over%20the%20year%20was%209.3%25%2C%20and%2050%20of%20the%2064%20downtowns%20saw%20increased%20activity%2C%20the%20researchers%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20of%20them%20have%20just%20sort%20of%20stagnated%20in%20their%20recovery%2C%26quot%3B%20Chapple%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20data%20aligned%20with%20office-building%20vacancy%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20University%20of%20Toronto%20researchers%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Institute%20of%20Governmental%20Studies%20at%20UC%20Berkeley%2C%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fschoolofcities.utoronto.ca%2Fdowntown-recovery%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalyzing%20foot%20traffic%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20January%202020%20to%20understand%20how%20downtowns%20are%20coping%20with%20the%20impacts%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20Chapple%20said%20it'd%20probably%20take%20years%20for%20many%20downtowns%20to%20attract%20the%20numbers%20they%20had%20pre-pandemic.%20Some%20probably%20never%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B2022%20was%20a%20big%20upswing%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20in%202023%2C%20that%20upswing%20slowed%20dramatically%2C%20and%20in%202024%20it's%20slowing%20even%20more%20because%20we've%20reached%20what%20people%20are%20calling%20the%20new%20normal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPandemic-induced%20remote%20work%20has%20exacerbated%20the%20decline%20of%20many%20downtowns%20that%20were%20struggling%20long%20before%20COVID-19%20hit%20and%20threatens%20to%20send%20many%20others%20into%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Burban%20doom%20loop.%26quot%3B%20As%20offices%20empty%20and%20residents%20leave%2C%20experts%20warn%20that%20declines%20in%20tax%20revenue%20could%20force%20the%20government%20to%20cut%20funding%20for%20municipal%20services%20such%20as%20schools%20and%20mass%20transit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertain%20downtowns%20haven't%20seen%20much%20progress%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20San%20Francisco%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20kept%20its%20spot%20in%20last%20place%20for%20downtown%20activity%2C%20seeing%20a%2021.6%25%20decline%20in%20foot%20traffic%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20But%20others%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20several%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmidwest-america-cities-downtown-crisis-office-apocalypse-urban-doom-loop-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMidwestern%20cities%20that%20struggled%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%8