Fwhat-is-the-israeli-netzah-yehuda-battalion-accused-of%2Famp_articleshow%2F109497729.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Exclusive%3A%20Palestine%20Family's%20Barefoot%20Dash%20To%20Escape%20Israeli%20Bombs%20In%20Gaza%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFor%20Amjad%20Shabat%20and%20her%20family%2C%20survival%20was%20the%20focus%2C%20and%20home%20was%20just%20an%20afterthought.%20A%20sign%20on%20an%20apartment%20next%20to%20hers%20read%20%26quot%3Bto%20be%20bombed%26quot%3B.%20A%20frantic%20search%20to%20grab%20anything%20essential%20and%20a%20barefooted%20dash%20across%20the%20street%20followed%20as%20the%20sound%20of%20Israeli%20drones%20and%20jets%20overhead%20indicated%20imminent%20death.%20That%20day%2C%20three%20days%20after%20the%20October%207%20attacks%20carried%20out%20by%20Hamas%20militants%20on%20Israeli%20soil%2C%20killing%20over%201%2C000%20people%2C%20Amjad's%20family's%20clock%20was%20reset.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmjad%2C%2033%2C%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20Gaza%20City%2C%20amidst%20the%20ever-present%20spectre%20of%20conflict.%20Once%20an%20English%20teacher%20with%20dreams%20of%20a%20better%20future%2C%20her%20life%20was%20upended%20by%20the%20violence%20that%20has%20plagued%20the%20region%20for%20generations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20used%20to%20be%20an%20English%20teacher%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20NDTV.%20%26quot%3BA%20year%20before%20the%20war%2C%20I%20bought%20my%20dream%20house%20along%20with%20my%20husband%2C%20a%20small%20flat%20on%20the%20coast%20with%20a%20view%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%26quot%3B%20For%20Amjad%20and%20her%20family%2C%20the%20modest%20comforts%20of%20home%20provided%20a%20respite%20from%20the%20harsh%20realities%20of%20life%20in%20Gaza%2C%20where%20basic%20necessities%20like%20electricity%20and%20clean%20water%20were%20often%20in%20short%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20there%20was%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued%2C%20her%20words%20echoing%20the%20sentiments%20of%20countless%20Palestinians%20who%20have%20long%20endured%20the%20hardships%20of%20living%20under%20occupation.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20shortage%20in%20all%20services.%20We%20used%20to%20get%20seven%20hours%20of%20electricity%20a%20day%20and%20lacked%20freshwater.%20The%20tap%20water%20was%20salty%20and%20polluted.%20There%20were%20few%20opportunities%20for%20people%20of%20my%20generation%20especially%20in%20the%20working%20sector.%20No%20parks%2C%20no%20cinema%2C%20no%20theatre.%20I%20am%20among%20the%20few%20of%20my%20generation%20who%20refused%20to%20migrate%20out%20of%20Gaza%20and%20instead%20decided%20to%20raise%20my%203-year-old%20daughter%20in%20the%20city%2C%20carrying%20hopes%20and%20dreams%20of%20a%20free%20Palestine%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20daily%20struggles%20of%20life%20in%20Gaza%20were%20compounded%20by%20the%20pervasive%20sense%20of%20isolation%20and%20despair%20that%20permeates%20every%20aspect%20of%20Palestinian%20life.%20%26quot%3BYoung%20Palestinians%20living%20in%20Gaza%20were%20denied%20the%20opportunity%20to%20travel%20abroad%2C%26quot%3B%20Amjad%20explained%2C%20her%20voice%20heavy%20with%20resignation.%20%26quot%3BIn%20order%20to%20travel%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20obtain%20numerous%20permissions%20from%20Israeli%20or%20Egyptian%20authorities%2C%20a%20very%20difficult%20process%20to%20undertake.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20The%20Run%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmjad's%20husband%2C%20Fadi%20Alshafei%2C%20is%20a%20journalist%20at%20a%20local%20news%20website.%20When%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20vowed%20to%20reduce%20Hamas%20hideouts%20in%20Gaza%20to%20%26quot%3Brubble%26quot%3B%2C%20Fadi%2C%20Amjad%20and%20their%20daughter%20Ghady%20were%20already%20apprehensive%20about%20their%20futures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remember%20three%20days%20after%20the%20October%207%20attacks%2C%20on%20an%20apartment%20next%20to%20our%20flat%2C%20was%20written%2C%20'to%20be%20bombed'.%20This%20prompted%20an%20urgent%20evacuation.%20However%2C%20we%20were%20confused%20as%20there%20was%20no%20official%20communication%20instructing%20us%20to%20leave%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Amjad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20glanced%20out%20of%20our%20window%20to%20witness%20a%20scene%20of%20chaos%3A%20people%20were%20screaming%20and%20fleeing%20in%20one%20direction.%20Gripped%20by%20panic%2C%20I%20clutched%20my%20daughter%20close%2C%20while%20my%20husband%20gathered%20our%20passports%20and%20essential%20documents.%20Barefoot%2C%20we%20fled%20our%20home%2C%20with%20my%20husband%20the%20only%20one%20to%20remember%20to%20put%20shoes%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BFortunately%2C%20my%20mother's%20residence%20was%20located%20at%20the%20end%20of%20our%20street.%20We%20sought%20refuge%20there%20for%20three%20days%20until%20October%2013%2C%20a%20Friday%20when%20the%20Israelis%20issued%20a%20call%20for%20evacuation%2C%20urging%20residents%20of%20northern%20Gaza%20to%20relocate%20to%20the%20south.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fhehkikq_gaza-palace-napoleon-bonaparte-_625x300_17_April_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2013th-century%20Al-Basha%20palace%20in%20Gaza%20City%2C%20where%20French%20emperor%20Napoleon%20Bonaparte%20once%20camped.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20relentless%20Israeli%20airstrikes%20mark%20the%20most%20intense%20aerial%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20in%20response%20to%20Hamas'%20deadliest%20attack%20on%20Israel%20in%20decades.%20Months%20of%20dropping%20bombs%20on%20the%20besieged%20Palestinian%20territory%20has%20destroyed%20ancient%20buildings%2C%20and%20monuments%2C%20including%20the%2013th-century%20Al-Basha%20palace%20in%20Gaza%20City%2C%20where%20French%20emperor%20Napoleon%20Bonaparte%20once%20camped.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20evacuated%20to%20the%20south%2C%26quot%3B%20Amjad%20recounted.%20%26quot%3BOur%20house%20was%20then%20destroyed%20in%20an%20airstrike%20sometime%20on%20October%2017%2C%20I%20think.%20We%20did%20not%20see%20it%2C%20we%20were%20sent%20photos%20by%20some%20friends%20who%20had%20gone%20back%20to%20check%20up%20on%20their%20houses.%20My%20mother's%20house%20is%20also%20destroyed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Blast%20Every%2020%20Seconds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForced%20to%20wander%20from%20one%20makeshift%20shelter%20to%20another%2C%20Amjad%20and%20her%20family%20found%20themselves%20living%20in%20a%20tent%20in%20Al%20Mawasi%2C%20a%20coastal%20city%20ravaged%20by%20war%20and%20deprivation.%20They%20had%20initially%20reached%20Rafah%20to%20stay%20at%20Fadi's%20father's%20house%20but%20had%20to%20leave%20because%20of%20overcrowding.%20Approximately%201.5%20million%20out%20of%20Gaza's%202.4%20million%20inhabitants%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20sought%20refuge%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20eventually%20ended%20up%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Khan%20Younis%20at%20Fadi's%20uncle's%20place%20but%20after%20Israeli%20tanks%20rolled%20into%20the%20city%20they%20had%20to%20evacuate%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSituation%20(in%20Al%20Mawasi)%20was%20catastrophic%2C%26quot%3B%20Amjad%20remembered.%20%26quot%3BWe%20shared%20a%20bathroom%20with%2040%20other%20people.%20I%20remember%20waking%20up%20very%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20to%20clean%20the%20bathroom%20so%20my%20daughter%20could%20use%20it%20half%20an%20hour%20later.%20I%20was%20terrified%20of%20her%20catching%20any%20disease.%20Especially%20considering%20how%20diseases%20were%20spreading%20in%20camps.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2