%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Way%20Out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20weeks%2C%20the%20family%20moved%20through%20the%20brutal%20landscape%20of%20Gaza%2C%20while%20fighting%20the%20constant%20threat%20of%20violence%20and%20despair.%20As%20thousands%20died%20every%20week%2C%20the%20family%2C%20short%20of%20money%2C%20tried%20desperately%20to%20get%20out%20of%20Gaza%20to%20provide%20their%20daughter%20a%20better%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20glimmer%20of%20opportunity%20emerged.%20Months%20ago%2C%20Amjad%20had%20applied%20for%20a%20scholarship%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20for%20a%20Master's%20in%20Middle%20Eastern%20Studies.%20An%20email%20regarding%20its%20outcome%20sat%20unread%20in%20her%20inbox.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remember%20receiving%20the%20letter%20for%20the%20scholarship%20in%20November%2C%20a%20month%20after%20the%20war%20started%2C%26quot%3B%20recalled%20Amjad.%20%26quot%3BAt%20that%20time%2C%20I%20lived%20in%20Khan%20Younis.%20We%20did%20not%20have%20good%20internet%2C%20but%20I%20somehow%20managed%20to%20get%20a%20connection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20boy%20stands%20by%20rubble%20before%20a%20heavily%20damaged%20building%20in%20the%20eastern%20side%20of%20the%20Maghazi%20camp%20for%20Palestinian%20refugees%20in%20the%20central%20Gaza%20Strip%20on%20April%2015%2C%202024%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20boy%20stands%20by%20rubble%20before%20a%20heavily%20damaged%20building%20in%20the%20eastern%20side%20of%20the%20Maghazi%20camp%20for%20Palestinian%20refugees%20in%20the%20central%20Gaza%20Strip%20on%20April%2015%2C%202024%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Ffrut4puo_gaza-afp-_625x300_22_April_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20boy%20stands%20by%20rubble%20before%20a%20heavily%20damaged%20building%20in%20the%20eastern%20side%20of%20the%20Maghazi%20camp%20for%20Palestinian%20refugees%20in%20the%20central%20Gaza%20Strip%20on%20April%2015%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20race%20against%20time%2C%20they%20reached%20out%20to%20contacts%20abroad%2C%20seeking%20urgent%20assistance%20to%20escape%20the%20horrors%20unfolding%20around%20them.%20%26quot%3BWe%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20hope%2C%20like%20light%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20very%20dark%20tunnel%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20reflected.%20%26quot%3BWe%20thought%20this%20is%20our%20life%20now%20-%20displaced%20and%20living%20in%20tents%20and%20refugee%20camps.%20Our%20daughter%20would%20be%20raised%20fighting%20diseases%20or%20worse%2C%20we%20could%20all%20get%20killed%20by%20an%20Israeli%20airstrike.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmjad's%20acceptance%20letter%20meant%20the%20family%20had%20provisions%20to%20apply%20for%20them%20being%20on%20a%20priority%20student's%20list%20-%20their%20ticket%20out%20of%20Gaza%20through%20the%20Rafah%20border%2C%20the%20only%20border%20crossing%20in%20Gaza%20that%20is%20not%20controlled%20by%20the%20Israeli%20government.%20So%20they%20applied%20for%20an%20US%20visa%20through%20its%20embassy%20in%20Cairo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20Palestinians%20have%20lost%20the%20sense%20of%20time.%20On%20October%207%20our%20clocks%20were%20reset.%20After%20four%20months%20of%20trying%20and%20finding%20means%20and%20ways%20to%20be%20evacuated%20from%20Gaza%20our%20name%20appeared%20in%20the%20student%20list.%20We%20discovered%20this%20by%20chance.%20Because%20there%20was%20no%20internet%2C%26quot%3B%20Amjad%20recounted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Escape%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20first%20day%20of%20Ramadan.%20Despite%20the%20hardships%2C%20the%20losses%20and%20the%20uncertain%20future%2C%20Amjad%20and%20her%20husband%20decided%20to%20celebrate%20the%20first%20day%20with%20family.%20With%20roads%20bombed%2C%20cars%20out%20of%20fuel%20and%20public%20transport%20shut%20down%2C%20they%20used%20carts%20pulled%20by%20donkeys%2C%20or%20horses%20to%20reach%20Rafah%20at%20Fadi's%20