taught%20at%20a%20women%E2%80%99s%20college.%20They%20challenged%20societal%20conditioning%20and%20traditional%20roles%2C%20and%20battled%20against%20all%20odds%20to%20give%20their%20two%20girls%20everything%20they%20needed%20to%20fulfil%20their%20dreams%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20that%20involved%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F326200%2Fecosoul-home-india-boston-sustainable-plastic-free-kitchenware-cutlery-sugarcane-palm%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eselling%20their%20suburban%20Mumbai%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20moving%20to%20a%20smaller%20apartment%20to%20fund%20Hardika%E2%80%99s%20undergraduate%20education%20in%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20supporting%20his%20own%20daughters%2C%20Hardika%E2%80%99s%20father%20also%20provided%20monetary%20aid%20to%20blind%20schools%20by%20sponsoring%20braille%20printers.%20The%20concept%20of%20giving%20back%20and%20its%20social%20impact%20was%20drilled%20into%20her.%20As%20an%20adult%2C%20when%20she%20found%20out%20about%20social%20entrepreneurship%20as%20an%20adult%2C%20she%20found%20the%20missing%20puzzle%20piece.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20after%2023%20years%20of%20being%20in%20the%20US%2C%20she%20returned%20to%20India%20in%202011%20to%20launch%20Kinara%20Capital.%20It%C2%A0%20provides%20unsecured%20loans%20to%20Micro%2C%20Small%20and%20Medium-sized%20Enterprises%20(MSMEs)%20within%2024-48%20hours%20and%20has%20helped%20over%201%2C25%2C000%20business%20owners%20so%20far.%20Her%20vision%20was%20to%20provide%20capital%20to%20small%20business%20owners%20so%20that%20everyone%20could%20expand%20their%20ventures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20business%20has%20a%20special%20focus%20on%20women%2C%20be%20it%20in%20their%20personal%20team%2C%20where%20almost%2060%20percent%20top%20management%20are%20women%2C%20or%20through%20their%20%E2%80%98HerVikas%E2%80%99%20programme%2C%20that%20provides%20discounted%20business%20loans%20for%2