rs%20in%20India.%20Here's%20what%20inspired%20her%20to%20start.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A84%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F347259%2Fhardika-shah-kinara-capital-msme-unsecured-loan-nbfc-small-businesses-medium-enterprises%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20A%20German%20Woman%20Living%20In%20Kerala%20Helped%20180%20People%20Start%20NGOs%20Across%20The%20World%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDisability%20creates%20a%20distinction%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20This%20was%20Pondicherry-based%20psychologist%20G%20Karthikeyan%E2%80%99s%20prime%20observation%20during%20the%2015%20years%20he%20spent%20working%20at%20an%20orphanage.%20Despite%20harmonious%20co-existence%20being%20a%20valued%20objective%2C%20Karthikeyan%20was%20quick%20to%20note%20that%20institutional%20care%20in%20India%20is%20not%20tailored%20to%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F343534%2Fsparsh-asian-paints-start-foundation-initiative-tactile-art-rajasthan-netraheen-kalyan-sangh-jaipur%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren%20with%20disabilities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDisabled%20children%20find%20it%20tough%20to%20integrate%20into%20mainstream%20society%2C%E2%80%9D%20his%20learnings%20taught%20him.%20And%20more%20often%20than%20not%2C%20this%20dependency%20would%20blanket%20the%20children%E2%80%99s%20futures%2C%20causing%20them%20to%20stay%20back%20at%20the%20facility%20even%20past%20adulthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20interactions%20with%20some%20of%20the%20disabled%20children%20led%20Karthikeyan%20to%20sense%20their%20eagerness%20to%20learn.%20If%20only%20there%20was%20a%20way%20to%20channel%20this%20into%20a%20project%20that%20would%20help%20these%20children%20use%20their%20skills%20to%20become%20independent%2C%20he%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENoble%2